        last_assistant_message: "<analysis>\nLet me trace through the entire conversation chronologically:\n\n1. **Session continuation**: This is a continuation from a previous conversation. The summary describes extensive prior work implementing MCP prompts across 4 layers (Proto → SDK → Orchestrator → Transport → Marketplace plugin). Steps 1-4 were completed. Step 5 was partially complete (prompts.go created, plugin.go updated, main.go NOT yet updated).\n\n2. **First action**: I read `cmd/main.go`, found test files, read both test files to understand patterns.\n\n3. **Completed Step 5**: Updated `cmd/main.go` to add `mp.RegisterPrompts(builder)` after `mp.RegisterTools(builder)`. Updated the comment to mention \"5 MCP prompts\".\n\n4. **Added tests**: \n   - `transport_test.go`: Added 7 new tests (TestInitializeHasPromptsCapability, TestPromptsList, TestPromptsGet, TestPromptsGetMissingName, TestPromptsListNetworkError, TestPromptDefinitionToMCP, TestPromptGetResponseToMCP)\n   - `plugin_test.go`: Added TestManifestBuilderWithPrompts, registered a \"greet\" test prompt in QUIC integration test, added ListPrompts/PromptGet/PromptGetNotFound subtests\n\n5. **Build & test**: All passed successfully.\n\n6. **User request**: \"now create a script on scripts to push changes to github using my gh and my config not claude config and create a pr and submit it then release the script must make all of this done\"\n\n7. **Research phase**: Read existing scripts (release.sh, sync-repos.sh, split-repos.sh), CI workflows (ci.yml, release.yml), orchestra.lock, Makefile, homebrew formula. Checked gh auth status (fadymondy, authenticated).\n\n8. **User follow-up**: \"don't forget to update maketplace docs for prompts\"\n\n9. **Created scripts/ship.sh**: Full pipeline script with 6 steps: build/test, commit, push/PR, sync sub-repos, tag/release, framework tag. Made it executable.\n\n10. **Updated marketplace docs**: Added MCP Prompts section to TOOLS_REFERENCE.md with all 5 prompts documented.\n\n11. **Updated release artifacts**: \n    - `.github/workflows/release.yml`: Added `tools-marketplace` binary to build and tarball\n    - `Makefile`: Added `tools-marketplace` to release target\n    - `packaging/homebrew/orchestra.rb`: Added `tools-marketplace` to install\n\n12. **Ran ship.sh v0.1.1 --skip-pr**: \n    - Build & test passed\n    - Committed 22 files\n    - Pushed to master\n    - Synced all 9 repos (some needed rebase retries)\n    - Tagged and released all 9 repos at v0.1.1\n    - Framework tag pushed\n    - FAILED at framework release: `--generate-release-notes` is wrong flag, should be `--generate-notes`\n\n13. **Fixed ship.sh**: Changed `--generate-release-notes` to `--generate-notes`. Manually created the framework release. Committed fix and pushed.\n\n14. **CI failures**: User reported multiple `go vet` errors across sub-repos:\n    - `sdk-go`: `undefined: pluginv1.PromptDefinition`\n    - `orchestrator`: `undefined: pluginv1.PluginManifest.GetProvidesPrompts`, `undefined: pluginv1.PromptDefinition`, etc.\n    - `plugin-transport-stdio`: `undefined: protocol.MCPPromptsCapability`, `undefined: pluginv1.PluginRequest_ListPrompts`, etc.\n    - `plugin-tools-marketplace`: `undefined: pluginv1.PromptGetRequest`, `undefined: pluginv1.PromptArgument`, etc.\n    - CLI: `go build ./cmd/` → \"build output 'cmd' already exists and is a directory\"\n\n15. **Root cause identified**: All `go.mod` files reference `gen-go v0.1.0` and `sdk-go v0.1.0`, but the new prompt types only exist in `v0.1.1`. Locally works because `go.work` overrides with local paths, but CI clones repos independently.\n\n16. **Fixed go.mod files**: Updated all 6 go.mod files (sdk-go, orchestrator, plugin-tools-features, plugin-transport-stdio, plugin-storage-markdown, plugin-tools-marketplace) to reference `v0.1.1` for gen-go and sdk-go.\n\n17. **User feedback**: \"you must consider this update steps on ship command\" — user wants the go.mod version bump to be part of the ship pipeline.\n\n18. **Updated ship.sh**: Added a new \"Step 2: Bump go.mod Versions\" that:\n    - Reads internal module paths from orchestra.lock\n    - Finds all go.mod files in libs/\n    - Replaces version references for internal modules with the release version\n    - Renumbered subsequent steps (commit became step 3, push became step 4, etc.)\n\n19. **Where we left off**: The ship.sh was being updated but we haven't yet:\n    - Verified the ship.sh changes work\n    - Committed the go.mod changes\n    - Re-synced and re-released\n\nAlso need the LOCK_FILE variable defined in ship.sh (it was in release.sh but not ship.sh).\n\nLet me also note the CLI build issue: `go build ./cmd/` fails because `cmd` is a directory. This is a separate issue from the sub-repo CIs trying to build without `-o` flag. The Makefile uses `-o` so it's fine.\n\nThe stray `cli` binary at repo root was also noted.\n</analysis>\n\n<summary>\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\n   - **Previous session**: Implement MCP prompts support in the marketplace plugin (full 4-layer pipeline: Proto → SDK → Orchestrator → Transport → Marketplace). Steps 1-4 were completed in prior context. Step 5 was partially done.\n   - **This session's first task**: Complete Step 5 (wire up prompts in `cmd/main.go`), add tests, build and verify.\n   - **Second task**: \"now create a script on scripts to push changes to github using my gh and my config not claude config and create a pr and submit it then release the script must make all of this done\" — Create a full ship pipeline script.\n   - **Third task**: \"don't forget to update maketplace docs for prompts\" — Update TOOLS_REFERENCE.md with prompt documentation.\n   - **Fourth task (implicit from CI failures)**: Fix `go vet` failures in sub-repos caused by go.mod files pointing to old dependency versions.\n   - **Fifth task**: \"you must consider this update steps on ship command\" — Integrate go.mod version bumping into the ship.sh pipeline so it doesn't happen again.\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - **MCP Protocol (2024-11-05)**: JSON-RPC over stdio with `prompts/list` and `prompts/get` methods\n   - **Orchestra Plugin Architecture**: QUIC + Protobuf + mTLS, star topology via orchestrator\n   - **Go workspace (go.work)**: Local development uses `go.work` which overrides module versions with local paths. CI does NOT use go.work — it clones each sub-repo independently and resolves dependencies via Go module proxy using the tagged versions in `go.mod`.\n   - **Monorepo → Multi-repo sync**: `sync-repos.sh` pushes `libs/*` contents to individual GitHub repos. `release.sh` tags and creates releases on each repo.\n   - **orchestra.lock**: Single source of truth for package list (9 packages: proto, gen-go, sdk-go, orchestrator, plugin-storage-markdown, plugin-tools-features, plugin-transport-stdio, plugin-tools-marketplace, cli)\n   - **Version dependency chain**: gen-go (generated protobuf) → sdk-go (plugin SDK) → all plugins. When proto changes, gen-go must be released first, then sdk-go, then all consumers must bump their go.mod.\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n\n   - **`libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/cmd/main.go`** — Plugin entry point. Added `mp.RegisterPrompts(builder)` call and updated comment.\n     ```go\n     mp.RegisterTools(builder)\n     mp.RegisterPrompts(builder)\n     ```\n\n   - **`libs/plugin-transport-stdio/internal/transport_test.go`** — Added 7 prompt tests:\n     - `TestInitializeHasPromptsCapability` — verifies `capabilities.prompts` is set in initialize response\n     - `TestPromptsList` — mock sender returns 2 prompts, verifies MCP format conversion\n     - `TestPromptsGet` — sends prompt get with arguments, verifies response messages\n     - `TestPromptsGetMissingName` — verifies InvalidParams error when name is missing\n     - `TestPromptsListNetworkError` — verifies InternalError on network failure\n     - `TestPromptDefinitionToMCP` — tests translator function with 2 arguments\n     - `TestPromptGetResponseToMCP` — tests translator with 2 messages (user + assistant)\n\n   - **`libs/sdk-go/plugin/plugin_test.go`** — Added prompt tests:\n     - `TestManifestBuilderWithPrompts` — verifies `ProvidesPrompts()` manifest builder\n     - QUIC integration test additions: registered a \"greet\" prompt handler, added `ListPrompts`, `PromptGet`, `PromptGetNotFound` subtests\n     ```go\n     srv.RegisterPrompt(\"greet\", \"Greeting prompt\", []*pluginv1.PromptArgument{\n         {Name: \"name\", Description: \"Name to greet\", Required: true},\n     }, func(ctx context.Context, req *pluginv1.PromptGetRequest) (*pluginv1.PromptGetResponse, error) {\n         name := req.Arguments[\"name\"]\n         if name == \"\" { name = \"World\" }\n         return &pluginv1.PromptGetResponse{\n             Description: \"Greeting prompt\",\n             Messages: []*pluginv1.PromptMessage{\n                 {Role: \"user\", Content: &pluginv1.ContentBlock{Type: \"text\", Text: \"Hello, \" + name + \"!\"}},\n             },\n         }, nil\n     })\n     ```\n\n   - **`scripts/ship.sh`** — NEW FILE. Full ship pipeline script (commit, push, PR, sync, release). Key details:\n     - Steps: 0 (preflight) → 1 (build/test) → 2 (bump go.mod versions) → 3 (commit) → 4 (push/PR) → 5 (sync sub-repos) → 6 (tag/release) → 7 (framework tag)\n     - Uses user's own `gh` auth, not Claude's\n     - Flags: `--dry-run`, `--skip-pr`, `--message`, `--branch`\n     - Step 2 (go.mod bump) reads `orchestra.lock` to find internal module paths, then `sed`s all go.mod files in `libs/`\n     - Step 2 was added AFTER the first ship run revealed the CI go.mod issue\n     - The LOCK_FILE variable is used but may not be defined in the current version (it's defined in release.sh but needs to be added to ship.sh)\n\n   - **`libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/docs/TOOLS_REFERENCE.md`** — Updated title to \"Tools & Prompts Reference\", added full \"MCP Prompts (5)\" section documenting all 5 prompts with parameter tables.\n\n   - **`.github/workflows/release.yml`** — Added `tools-marketplace` binary to build step and tarball packaging.\n\n   - **`Makefile`** — Added `tools-marketplace` to the `release` target (build, tarball, cleanup).\n\n   - **`packaging/homebrew/orchestra.rb`** — Added `bin.install \"tools-marketplace\"`.\n\n   - **`orchestra.lock`** — Updated to `v0.1.1` by release.sh.\n\n   - **go.mod files (6 files)** — ALL bumped from `gen-go v0.1.0` / `sdk-go v0.1.0` to `v0.1.1`:\n     - `libs/sdk-go/go.mod` — gen-go v0.1.0 → v0.1.1\n     - `libs/orchestrator/go.mod` — gen-go + sdk-go v0.1.0 → v0.1.1\n     - `libs/plugin-tools-features/go.mod` — gen-go + sdk-go v0.1.0 → v0.1.1\n     - `libs/plugin-transport-stdio/go.mod` — gen-go + sdk-go v0.1.0 → v0.1.1\n     - `libs/plugin-storage-markdown/go.mod` — gen-go + sdk-go v0.1.0 → v0.1.1\n     - `libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/go.mod` — gen-go + sdk-go v0.1.0 → v0.1.1\n\n4. Errors and fixes:\n   - **`--generate-release-notes` flag error**: ship.sh used `--generate-release-notes` but gh CLI expects `--generate-notes`. Fixed by editing ship.sh and manually creating the framework release with `gh release create v0.1.1 --repo \"orchestra-mcp/framework\" --title \"v0.1.1\" --generate-notes`.\n   \n   - **CI `go vet` failures across all sub-repos**: After v0.1.1 release, CI in every sub-repo failed with `undefined: pluginv1.PromptDefinition` and similar errors. Root cause: go.mod files in each lib still referenced `gen-go v0.1.0` and `sdk-go v0.1.0` which don't have the new prompt types. Locally it worked because `go.work` overrides versions. Fixed by bumping all 6 go.mod files to `v0.1.1`. User then requested this be automated in ship.sh.\n     - User explicitly said: \"you must consider this update steps on ship command\"\n   \n   - **CLI build error** (`go build ./cmd/` → \"build output 'cmd' already exists and is a directory\"): This happens when running `go build ./cmd/` without `-o` flag inside repos that have a `cmd/` directory. The Makefile and release workflow both use `-o` so it doesn't affect them. This seems to be from a sub-repo CI or manual invocation. Not yet fixed in CI configs.\n\n   - **Duplicate `---` in TOOLS_REFERENCE.md**: The edit produced two consecutive `---` separators (line 157 and 159). Minor formatting issue, not addressed.\n\n   - **LOCK_FILE variable missing in ship.sh**: The new Step 2 in ship.sh references `${LOCK_FILE}` but this variable is only defined in release.sh, not in ship.sh. This will cause a runtime error. Needs to be added.\n\n5. Problem Solving:\n   - Successfully completed the full MCP prompts implementation across all 4 layers\n   - Created a comprehensive ship pipeline that automates: build → test → go.mod bump → commit → push/PR → sync → release → framework tag\n   - Identified and fixed the go.mod version pinning issue that caused CI failures\n   - Identified that the ship script needs to include go.mod version bumping as an automated step\n   - Still need to: commit the go.mod fixes, re-sync repos, and re-release (v0.1.2)\n\n6. All user messages:\n   - (Session continuation message with full context of prior work)\n   - \"now create a script on scripts to push changes to github using my gh and my config not claude config and create a pr and submit it then release the script must make all of this done\"\n   - \"don't forget to update maketplace docs for prompts\"\n   - User selected \"v0.1.1\" when asked about version\n   - \"Run go vet ./... → sdk-go error: plugin/server.go:40:23: undefined: pluginv1.PromptDefinition\"\n   - \"Run go vet ./... → orchestrator errors: router.go multiple undefined types\"\n   - \"Run go build ./cmd/ → go: build output 'cmd' already exists and is a directory\"\n   - \"Run go vet ./... → plugin-transport-stdio errors: handler.go, translator.go undefined types\"\n   - \"Run go vet ./... → plugin-tools-marketplace errors: prompts.go undefined types\"\n   - \"you must consider this update steps on ship command\"\n\n7. Pending Tasks:\n   - **Fix LOCK_FILE variable in ship.sh**: The new Step 2 uses `${LOCK_FILE}` but it's not defined. Need to add `LOCK_FILE=\"${ROOT}/orchestra.lock\"` near the top of ship.sh.\n   - **Commit go.mod changes + ship.sh updates**: The go.mod bumps to v0.1.1 and the ship.sh Step 2 addition need to be committed and pushed.\n   - **Re-sync all 9 repos**: The go.mod changes need to be synced to sub-repos so CI passes.\n   - **Re-release as v0.1.2**: Need to ship a new version with the fixed go.mod files so that CI in all sub-repos passes `go vet`.\n   - **Optional: Fix CLI `go build ./cmd/` issue**: Add `-o` flag to any CI that builds from `cmd/` directories.\n   - **Optional: Fix stray `cli` binary at repo root**: A compiled binary was accidentally committed.\n\n8. Current Work:\n   I was in the middle of updating `scripts/ship.sh` to add a new \"Step 2: Bump go.mod Versions\" that automatically updates all internal dependency versions in go.mod files before committing. The edit was applied — I added the new step between build/test and commit, which:\n   - Reads internal module paths from `orchestra.lock`  \n   - Finds all `go.mod` files in `libs/`\n   - Uses `sed` to replace version references for internal modules with the release version\n   \n   However, there's a bug: the script references `${LOCK_FILE}` which is not defined in ship.sh (it's defined in release.sh). The go.mod files have already been manually edited to v0.1.1 but haven't been committed, synced, or released yet.\n\n9. Optional Next Step:\n   Fix the `LOCK_FILE` variable bug in ship.sh (add `LOCK_FILE=\"${ROOT}/orchestra.lock\"` at the top), then run the ship pipeline to release v0.1.2 with the corrected go.mod versions. This directly addresses the user's request: \"you must consider this update steps on ship command\" and the CI failures they reported.\n\n   The ship.sh step 2 code that was just added references `${LOCK_FILE}` but this variable needs to be defined. After fixing that, we need to ship v0.1.2 to resolve all the CI `go vet` failures across the sub-repos.\n</summary>"
